description:
‚Å£Caprese Chicken with Pesto üåøüçÖ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This dish is a perfect light dinner for the warm weather we‚Äôve been having and so easy to cook with hardly any ingredients needed! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Ingredients:‚†Ä
üçÖ1 chicken breast‚†Ä
üçÖ1 ball mozarella cheese ‚†Ä
üçÖ2 tomatoes ‚†Ä
üçÖsmall handful of basil ‚†Ä
üçÖpesto ‚†Ä
üçÖbalsamic glaze ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the chicken: ‚†Ä
preheat the oven to 180 degrees ‚†Ä
Chop your tomatoes ans mozarella into even slices ‚†Ä
Cut slices into the chicken breast deep enough for the stuffing ‚†Ä
Place the chicken breast on the oven tray and place slices of mozarella and tomato into the slices made in the chicken ‚†Ä
Top with 2 teaspoons of pesto, salt & pepper‚†Ä
Cook in the oven for roughly 30 mins till the chicken is cooked through ‚†Ä
Top with fresh basil & serve ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the caprese salad:‚†Ä
Lay out even slices of tomato and mozarella on your plate ‚†Ä
Lightly drizzle olive oil & balsamic glaze‚†Ä
Top with salt, pepper & fresh basil ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Enjoy! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This was delicious and minimum effort so is perfect for a weekday meal üòã‚†Ä

description:
Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

‚ú®Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce‚ú®

Ingredients:
‚úÖ2 lb bok choy, small 
‚úÖ1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
‚úÖ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
‚úÖ1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ‚úÖ6 Tbs tamari sauce 
‚úÖ1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds.

description:
Sweet & Savoury Mushroom Scones~üçÑ This easy and quick snack made with our favourite mushrooms is definitely a pleaser. We love having them with cream cheese, random toppings and even on its own.üòã Mama also made them petite so it's easy to pack them along as mini treats for the kids' outings! ‚ù§
.
Ingredients:
200g swiss brown mushrooms, chopped 
220g all purpose flour
20g sugar
6g baking powder
¬Ω tsp salt
1 tsp #lilomushroompowder
55g cold butter, cut into small cubes
25g beaten egg
Approx. 100ml milk 
.
Method:
‚úîIn a pan, saut√© chopped mushrooms with some butter till slightly brown and set aside to cool
‚úîCombine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and #lilomushroompowder in a bowl
‚úîRub in butter cubes with fingers until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs before adding in the saut√©ed mushrooms 
‚úîAdd in beaten egg and milk, and mix with a spatula until just combined with no dry flour remaining (add more milk if required)
‚úîTurn the dough out onto a floured surface and sprinkle some flour on top
‚úîPat the dough down lightly to about 3cm thick and cut straight down with a round cutter without twisting it
‚úîGather the loose pieces of dough into a ball and pat down again to cut out more
‚úîBrush the top of the scones with egg and bake in a preheated oven for 15-20 minutes at 180¬∞C till golden brown
.
.
.

description:
overnight oats üçØ if you‚Äôre wanting some easy and deLISH breakfast inspiration, you need these overnight oats at the top of your list! I‚Äôve been making it in 3-day batches and I can‚Äôt get enough ü§§ recipe below - brands tagged for reference!

Overnight oats (makes 3 portions)

Ingredients:
- 1.5 cups @quakeroatsuk oats
- 2 scoops unflavoured or vanilla @bulk protein powder
- 1/2 tsp cinnamon
- 1.5-2 cups milk of choice (I use @alpro) 
- 2/3 cup greek yoghurt
- 2 tbsp chia seeds
- maple syrup to taste (I used about 1 tbsp)
- 1 tsp vanilla essence (omit if using vanilla protein)
- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips

method:
- mix together the oats, protein powder and cinnamon
- add the rest of the ingredients and mix together until we‚Äôll combined
- pour into an airtight container (or multiple if you want them in pre-prepped portions)
- store in the fridge for up to three days. Serve topped with fresh strawberries üçì and @pipandnut peanut butter

description:
Finally got round to making baba ganoush! Not sure why but I thought it was going to be way more effort than it was. TASTED UNBELIEVABLE ü§§ no blender needed. 

Ingredients: 
2 aubergines 
2 minced garlic cloves 
2 tablespoons lemon juice 
1/4 cup tahini 
1/3 cup olive oil 
2 tbsp chopped flat leaf parsley
1/4 tsp cumin 
Salt n peps 
Sprinkle of paprika 

Method:
~ preheat oven to 230 degrees c 
~ chop your aubergines in half lengthwise and brush cut sides with olive oil 
~ place them skin side up on baking paper lined tray and bake in oven for 35-40 mins 
~ when done, scoop out aubergine flesh and strain flesh to get rid of liquid 
~ put in bowl, add garlic and lemon juice, and whisk with a fork to break down the aubergine 
~ add tahini and stir till combined 
~ while stirring, slowly drizzle in olive oil 
~ once all broken down and mixed together, add in salt, cumin and parsley 
~ add more lemon juice to taste 
~ transfer to a pretty bowl and drizzle with more olive oil and a sprinkle of paprika and parsley 

Voila! I chopped up some pitta breads and roasted them in olive oil, salt n peps and rosemary to scoop up the deliciousness with. 

#babaganoush #aubergine #foodie #foodism #foodismedicine #foodislife #recipe #recipeoftheday #recipeideas

description:
Recipe time!!

Boil your lasagna for 5-7 minutes and run cold water over it once its boiled! Keep it aside.

Chicken Minced Ingredients: 

- Half kg Chicken minced
- 1 Medium sized Onion finely chopped 
- 3-4 medium sized tomatoes (paste)
- Ginger garlic paste 2 TB spoon (Because I LOVEEE)
- Salt (as per taste)
- Paprika powder, 1 TB spoon (or as per your taste)
- Oregano (half tea spoon)
- Mixed Herms (as per your liking)
- Soya sauce 1 TB spoon
- Chilli sauce 1 TB spoon
- Chilli garlic ketchup (3-4 TB spoons ü•Ñ)

Method: Saut√© your onion in half tb spoon oil, add ginger garlic paste and cook it until your onion becomes transparent, add chicken minced and saut√© nicely for about 4-5 Mins, add tomato paste, all the spices and sauces and let it cook for almost 20 mins or until the water dries up.

White Sauce Ingredients:
- Butter (3-4 TB spoon)
- Maida- all purpose flour - (4-5 TB spoon)
- Milk around 1-1.5 Cups, depends on your consistency
- Black pepper (1 tea spoon)
- Salt (as per your liking)
- White pepper (1 tea spoon)
- Oregano (half tea spoon)
- Mixed herbs (half tea spoon)

Method: Add butter in your pan, once its melted, add flour and keep wisking, gradually add milk while mixing the mixture, add all your spices and herbs, make sure you‚Äôre continuously mixing so there‚Äôs no lumps in the sauce. Once you get your desired consistency, turn off the flame. 

Preparation: In a ovenproof dish, Make a layer of your lasagna sheets, top it with your minced mixture, drop some white sauce on it, garnish with mushrooms and olives, put some (A LOT) cheese, I used mozzarella and cheddar!

Keep repeating the layers! Make the last layer of lasagna sheet, mushrooms, olives, Oregano and cheese.
Bake it for 20-25 mins, once its done, Broil it for 5-7 mins or once the cheese is completely melted and the crust is nicely golden! ü§ç 

TADAAA! Done.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.

I adapted this recipe by adding chicken for protein, more veggies and omitting the parmesan to serve, although this is also fine if you choose to add it.

‚ú¥Ô∏èINGREDIENTS:
1 tbsp olive oil
1 leek, finely sliced
1/2 fennel bulb, thinly sliced
3 garlic cloves, crushed
1/2 tsp fennel seeds
6 sprigs oregano, or 1 1/2 tsp dried leaves

üçãùó£ùóÆùóøùòÄùóπùó≤ùòÜ, ùóîùóπùó∫ùóºùóªùó± ùóÆùóªùó± ùóüùó≤ùó∫ùóºùóª ùó¶ùóÆùóπùòÄùóÆ (optional but super delicious and you only need a tsp or two)

40mL olive oil

‚ú¥Ô∏èMETHOD:
1Ô∏è‚É£ Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat. Add leek, fennel, celery, garlic, fennel seeds and oregano and cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes until softened and lightly golden.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Season, add parmesan rind, stock and 1 cup water and bring to a simmer. Add chicken pieces and cook for 10 minutes or until chicken is just cooked through.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Remove chicken pieces and allow to cool slightly. Add zucchini, cannelini beans and silverbeet and stir for 3-4 minutes or until zucchini is just softened. Shred chicken, return to saucepan and stir. 

4Ô∏è‚É£ Meanwhile for the salsa, simply blend together all ingredients in thermomix or food processor.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Remove parmesan rind and serve. Top with salsa if using, and fresh, torn parsley leaves. üòã

description:
I love the convenience and ease of meals like this. Be sure to screen shot or save this recipe to make you life healthier and easier! These are super to pack in a cooler and take down on the beach or to the lake! 

Cheeseburger Mason Jar Salad

4 servings 
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp ground black pepper
‚Ä¢ ¬Ω cup thinly sliced cucumber
‚Ä¢ 4, quart-sized mason jars
‚Ä¢ 1¬º lb. 90% lean ground beef
‚Ä¢ 6 tbsp lemon juice
‚Ä¢ 8 cups chopped leaf lettuce
‚Ä¢ 4 oz. reduced-fat, shredded cheddar cheese
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp salt, divided
‚Ä¢ 2 scallions, chopped
‚Ä¢ 1 cup diced fresh tomatoes
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup water
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup white vinegar
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp yellow mustard

Directions: 

1. Heat up a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Spray pan with non-stick spray.

2. Add ground beef and brown all sides, breaking up any clumps; season with salt and pepper. Drain and allow to cool.

3. Bring vinegar, water, and a pinch of salt to a boil. Pour liquid over cucumbers and set aside to make pickles. Drain the juice when ready to serve.

4. Whisk together the mustard and lemon juice to make a vinaigrette.

5. For 1 portion, fill a quart-sized mason jar with 1¬Ω tablespoons of lemon mustard vinaigrette, ¬º cup of tomatoes, 4 ounces cooked ground beef, 2 tablespoons of pickles, 2 cups lettuce, 1 ounce of shredded cheese, and ¬º of the scallions. 

For our clients on program, this breaks down to:
1 lean - 3 greens - 0 healthy fats - 3 condiments (per serving)

description:
FIT INTO YOUR BIKINI TAHINI
Ingredients: 
1/2 cup tahini
Juice of 1/2 lemon
1 tbsp of olive oil
cold water
Salt and Pepper 
Dried Parsley

Romaine
Tomatoes
Persian cucumber 
Pine nuts 
Sliced Almonds 

Directions:
Finely chop all veggies for the salad. The key to great lettuce is a thin chop. Bunch the leaves together tightly and chop!! Make sure you pat dry after rinsing or it will get soggy. 

For the dressing: combine tahini, olive oil, and lemon juice. Stir! It will be thick. Slowly pour small amounts of very cold water till the tahini thins out while constantly stirring with a spoon or fork. Keep adding water till you get the consistency you desire. Then add in your parsley, salt, and pepper. Pour on top of your salad and enjoy.
